The evidence with the title 'Shoe-banging incident - Wikipedia ' says Nikita Khrushchev's shoe-banging incident occurred during the 902nd Plenary Meeting of the United Nations General Assembly held in New York in 1960 . During the session on 12 october , Nikita Khrushchev, first secretary of the Communist Party Of the Soviet Union , pounded his shoe on his delegate-desk in protest  ... He also reported that no photographic or video records of the shoe- banging  ... 
